OL,3,CMan's loyalist 'show of strength'
OL,4,Cconviction quashed by appeal court
OL,6,F"We don't know the last time these two
OL,7,Fofficers heard Mr Lammey's voice, if
OL,8,Fever."
OL,10,FProsecutors accepted a proper warning
OL,11,Fwas not given about the potential
OL,12,Fdangers of relying on voice
OL,13,Frecognition from non-experts in
OL,14,Fcriminal cases.
OL,16,FBacking the defence's case, Lady Chief
OL,17,FJustice Dame Siobhan Keegan held that
OL,18,Fit would have highlighted frailties in
OL,19,Fthe evidence.
