OL,3,CMan's loyalist 'show of strength'
OL,4,Cconviction quashed by appeal court
OL,6,F"Identification by voice is even less
OL,7,Freliable than eye-witness
OL,8,Fidentification or recognition," she
OL,9,Fsaid.
OL,11,F"Even a confident recognition of a
OL,12,Ffamiliar voice by a lay listener may
OL,13,Fnevertheless be wrong."
OL,15,FDame Siobhen, sitting with Lord
OL,16,FJustice Colton and Mr Justice O'Hara,
OL,17,Fstressed this was the evidence which
OL,18,Fhad "tipped the balance" into Lammey
OL,19,Fbeing found guilty.
